				<div id="romania"">
              <a name="romania"></a><h2>Romania</h2>
              <p><strong><img src="../../images/kids-romania.jpg" width="250" height="188" hspace="10" align="right"><span class="plaintext">Home Makeover</span></strong><span class="plaintext"><br>
                <br>
                In Fall 2006, Club Penguin partnered with an  international organization and Romanian social workers to improve the home of  one family in the village   of Budila. The renovation  has provided this family with a healthier and more stable environment.</span></p>
              <p> <span class="plaintext"><strong>Brasov Children&rsquo;s Hospital </strong><br>
                <br>
              Overcrowded hospitals and abandoned children, combined with a severe shortage of orphanages and foster care, has left a great number of Romanian children in need of help. </span></p>
              <p class="plaintext"> Club Penguin is helping one organization address this need through the Brasov Children&rsquo;s Hospital Project. This undertaking will provide care for abandoned children and work toward reintegrating children with their families where possible. </p>
              <p class="plaintext">Renovation of hospital rooms has begun and a team  of social workers and caregivers is in place to help.</p>
              <p> <span class="plaintext"><strong>Meal and Education Program<br>
                </strong><br>
              This project provides children who are having difficulty in school and combating malnutrition with extra help in several villages and towns.<br>
              <br>
              Children are selected by the local school board, and given the opportunity to attend the program where they receive lunch, after class help, computer training and specialized one on one care.<br>
              <br>
  For more information on our work in Romania,  please contact
